Description: Two joining fragments of a Fikellura painted pottery neck-amphora. Shoulder, myrtle wreath. Belly, crescents.
Curator's comments: BSA xxxic,13 (G 6), 14, 74. Attributed to the Mykonos Group With BM GR 1888,0206.54.e-f (previously registered as 1924,1201.1070 and 1076) and 1888,0208.54.h (previously registered as 1924,1201.1078).Original height of complete amphora 25 cm.
Bibliographic references: CVA British Museum 8 / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum: Great Britain 13, British Museum 8 (Pl. G. B. 577, 4)
Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (pl. xxxii, 2)
Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 205)
